intro: Symphorema paniculatum, commonly known as the panicled symphorema, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Myrtaceae, which includes eucalyptus and tea trees. The plant is characterized by its erect, slender stems and clusters of small, white or pale pink flowers. Its leaves are narrow and often have a slight aromatic scent. It typically grows in sandy or rocky soils and is adapted to dry, coastal environments.
